The paper presents a data structure for summarizing update data streams, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces algorithms for answering various stream queries, which falls under the category of algorithms (cs.AL). The use of probabilistic techniques for finding approximate frequent items, quantiles, and hierarchical heavy hitters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the use of near-optimal $B$-bucket histograms, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
